A highly customizable multi-step form framework for Webflow.

The form is built using Webflow's native form builder.

## Steps

Each step is a <fieldset> element with a `step` attribute.

## Step Types:

### Checkboxes

A multi-select checkbox step. Use Webflow's native checkbox elements.

Supports an additional "Other" option. Implement it as a <div> with the `data-type="other"` attribute, containing an <input> and a label <label> (they don't have to be direct children).

```html
<div data-type="other">
  <label>...</label>
  <input type="text" />
</div>
```

### Radio Buttons

A single-select radio button step. Use Webflow's native radio button elements.

Supports an additional "Other" option, implemented the same way as the checkbox step.

### Text Input

A text input step. Supports `textarea`, `input[type="text"]` and `input[type="url"]`.

Implement custom validation using the [Constraint Validation API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation#complex_constraints_using_the_constraint_validation_api).
